        "introTitle": "What is ReliefConnect?",
        "introContent": "ReliefConnect is a relief connection platform that helps connect people in need with those who want to help in emergency situations like natural disasters and floods. You can send relief requests, search for support, or become a volunteer or sponsor.",
        "registerTitle": "Registration & Login",
        "registerContent": "Create an account and log in to use all features. After registering, you can verify your role (Person in Need, Volunteer, Sponsor) to access appropriate features.",
        "verifyTitle": "Role Verification",
        "verifyContent": "Go to the Verify tab in the sidebar, choose your role, upload ID photos, and submit. Admin will review and approve your request.",
        "sosTitle": "How to Send a Relief Request (SOS)",
        "sosContent": "Press the red SOS button on the right side of the screen. Select the request type (Need Help, Want to Give, Shelter), add a detailed description of your needs. Your request will be displayed on the map so others can help.",
        "mapTitle": "Using the Map",
        "mapContent": "The interactive map shows all active relief requests, supply points, and shelters. Use filters to narrow down by type. Click any marker for details. You can also view high-risk zones highlighted in red.",
        "filterTitle": "Filters & Search",
        "filterContent": "Use the filter bar at the top to show/hide different request types: Need Help, Offering, Supply Points, and Shelters. This helps you find exactly what you need.",
        "volunteerTitle": "Become a Volunteer",
        "volunteerContent": "Volunteers help distribute relief supplies and provide support in affected areas. Register for role verification to be assigned appropriate tasks.",
        "sponsorTitle": "Become a Sponsor",
        "sponsorContent": "Sponsors provide necessities, money, or other resources to help those in need. You can post relief information on the Community page.",
        "communityTitle": "Community Posts",
        "communityContent": "Share updates, ask for help, or offer support through the Community panel. You can create posts with images, react, and comment on others' posts.",
